      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import cvxpy as cp\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Basic linear-algebra helpers\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def kron(*args):\n",
        "    out = np.array([[1.0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for a in args:\n",
        "        out = np.kron(out, a)\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "def dagger(a):\n",
        "    return np.conjugate(a.T)\n",
        "\n",
        "def partial_trace(rho, dims, keep):\n",
        "    dims = list(dims)\n",
        "    n = len(dims)\n",
        "    keep = list(keep)\n",
        "    trace_over = [i for i in range(n) if i not in keep]\n",
        "    reshaped = rho.reshape(dims + dims)\n",
        "    for t in sorted(trace_over, reverse=True):\n",
        "        reshaped = np.trace(reshaped, axis1=t, axis2=t + n)\n",
        "        dims.pop(t)\n",
        "    d_keep = int(np.prod(dims)) if dims else 1\n",
        "    return reshaped.reshape(d_keep, d_keep)\n",
        "\n",
        "def von_neumann_entropy(rho, eps=1e-12):\n",
        "    rho = 0.5 * (rho + dagger(rho))\n",
        "    w = np.linalg.eigvalsh(rho)\n",
        "    w = np.clip(np.real(w), 0.0, 1.0)\n",
        "    w = w[w > eps]\n",
        "    return float(-np.sum(w * np.log(w)))\n",
        "\n",
        "def mutual_information(rho_ab, dims=(2, 2)):\n",
        "    rho_a = partial_trace(rho_ab, list(dims), keep=[0])\n",
        "    rho_b = partial_trace(rho_ab, list(dims), keep=[1])\n",
        "    return von_neumann_entropy(rho_a) + von_neumann_entropy(rho_b) - von_neumann_entropy(rho_ab)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Pauli matrices\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "I2 = np.eye(2, dtype=complex)\n",
        "X = np.array([[0, 1], [1, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Y = np.array([[0, -1j], [1j, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Z = np.array([[1, 0], [0, -1]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Channels via Kraus operators\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def apply_kraus(rho, kraus_ops):\n",
        "    out = np.zeros_like(rho, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for K in kraus_ops:\n",
        "        out += K @ rho @ dagger(K)\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "def depolarizing_kraus(p):\n",
        "    p = float(p)\n",
        "    k0 = np.sqrt(max(0.0, 1.0 - p)) * I2\n",
        "    kx = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * X\n",
        "    ky = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * Y\n",
        "    kz = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * Z\n",
        "    return [k0, kx, ky, kz]\n",
        "\n",
        "def unitary_kraus(U):\n",
        "    return [U]\n",
        "\n",
        "def channel_kraus_product(kraus_A, kraus_B):\n",
        "    return [kron(Ka, Kb) for Ka in kraus_A for Kb in kraus_B]\n",
        "\n",
        "def compose_kraus(kraus_after, kraus_before):\n",
        "    return [Ka @ Kb for Kb in kraus_before for Ka in kraus_after]\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Toy physical channel E_{theta,p}\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def U_xx(theta):\n",
        "    XX = kron(X, X)\n",
        "    return np.cos(theta) * np.eye(4, dtype=complex) - 1j * np.sin(theta) * XX\n",
        "\n",
        "def E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p):\n",
        "    U = U_xx(theta)\n",
        "    K_unit = unitary_kraus(U)\n",
        "    K_noise = channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(p), depolarizing_kraus(p))\n",
        "    return compose_kraus(K_noise, K_unit)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Choi matrix and diamond norm SDP\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def choi_from_kraus(kraus_ops, d_in, d_out):\n",
        "    J = np.zeros((d_out*d_in, d_out*d_in), dtype=complex)\n",
        "    basis = np.eye(d_in, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for i in range(d_in):\n",
        "        for j in range(d_in):\n",
        "            Eij = np.outer(basis[:, i], basis[:, j].conj())\n",
        "            Phi_Eij = apply_kraus(Eij, kraus_ops)\n",
        "            J += np.kron(Phi_Eij, Eij)\n",
        "    return J\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_norm_from_choi(J, d_in, d_out, solver=None, verbose=False):\n",
        "    dimX = d_out * d_in\n",
        "    rho = cp.Variable((d_in, d_in), complex=True)\n",
        "    Xvar = cp.Variable((dimX, dimX), complex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    Iout = np.eye(d_out, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    I_rho = cp.kron(Iout, rho)\n",
        "\n",
        "    block = cp.bmat([[I_rho, Xvar],\n",
        "                     [Xvar.H, I_rho]])\n",
        "\n",
        "    constraints = [\n",
        "        block >> 0,\n",
        "        rho >> 0,\n",
        "        cp.trace(rho) == 1\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    objective = cp.Maximize(cp.real(cp.trace(J @ Xvar)))\n",
        "    prob = cp.Problem(objective, constraints)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if solver is None:\n",
        "        solver = cp.SCS\n",
        "\n",
        "    prob.solve(solver=solver, verbose=verbose, eps=1e-5)\n",
        "    if prob.value is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"Diamond norm SDP returned None; try a different solver or relax eps.\")\n",
        "    return float(prob.value)\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_F, d_in=4, d_out=4, solver=None):\n",
        "    J_E = choi_from_kraus(kraus_E, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    J_F = choi_from_kraus(kraus_F, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    return diamond_norm_from_choi(J_E - J_F, d_in, d_out, solver=solver, verbose=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Symmetric admissible family (fast):\n",
        "#   C_q = (D_q  D_q)\n",
        "# and we estimate: delta(theta,p) = min_q || E_{theta,p} - C_q ||_diamond\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def C_q_kraus(q):\n",
        "    return channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(q), depolarizing_kraus(q))\n",
        "\n",
        "def estimate_delta_min_over_q(theta, p, q_grid, solver=None):\n",
        "    kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p)\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    best_q = None\n",
        "    for q in q_grid:\n",
        "        kraus_C = C_q_kraus(q)\n",
        "        dn = diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_C, solver=solver)\n",
        "        if (best is None) or (dn < best):\n",
        "            best = dn\n",
        "            best_q = q\n",
        "    return best, best_q\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Two inputs: |00> and |++>\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def ket0():\n",
        "    return np.array([1, 0], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def ket1():\n",
        "    return np.array([0, 1], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def ket_plus():\n",
        "    return (1/np.sqrt(2)) * (ket0() + ket1())\n",
        "\n",
        "def rho_from_ket(ket):\n",
        "    return np.outer(ket, ket.conj())\n",
        "\n",
        "def build_inputs():\n",
        "    ket00 = kron(ket0(), ket0())\n",
        "    ketpp = kron(ket_plus(), ket_plus())\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"|00>\": rho_from_ket(ket00),\n",
        "        \"|++>\": rho_from_ket(ketpp),\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Run sweep + plots\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def run_sweep(thetas, ps, q_grid, solver=cp.SCS, print_rows=True):\n",
        "    inputs = build_inputs()\n",
        "    I_maps = {name: np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps))) for name in inputs.keys()}\n",
        "    delta_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    q_best_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        for j, p in enumerate(ps):\n",
        "            kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(th, p)\n",
        "\n",
        "            for name, rho0 in inputs.items():\n",
        "                rho_out = apply_kraus(rho0, kraus_E)\n",
        "                I_maps[name][i, j] = mutual_information(rho_out, dims=(2, 2))\n",
        "\n",
        "            d_est, q_best = estimate_delta_min_over_q(th, p, q_grid, solver=solver)\n",
        "            delta_map[i, j] = d_est\n",
        "            q_best_map[i, j] = q_best\n",
        "\n",
        "            if print_rows:\n",
        "                print(f\"theta={th:.3f}, p={p:.3f}  ->  \"\n",
        "                      f\"I00={I_maps['|00>'][i,j]:.4f},  Ipp={I_maps['|++>'][i,j]:.4f},  \"\n",
        "                      f\"delta~{d_est:.4f} (q*={q_best:.3f})\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return I_maps, delta_map, q_best_map\n",
        "\n",
        "def heatmap(data, thetas, ps, title):\n",
        "    plt.figure()\n",
        "    plt.imshow(\n",
        "        data.T,\n",
        "        origin=\"lower\",\n",
        "        aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "        extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]]\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.colorbar()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Parameters (fast + meaningful)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "thetas = np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 7)\n",
        "ps = np.linspace(0.0, 0.6, 7)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Refine q-grid: this is now cheap enough to densify\n",
        "q_grid = np.linspace(0.0, 0.9, 41)\n",
        "\n",
        "I_maps, delta_map, q_best_map = run_sweep(\n",
        "    thetas=thetas,\n",
        "    ps=ps,\n",
        "    q_grid=q_grid,\n",
        "    solver=cp.SCS,\n",
        "    print_rows=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps[\"|00>\"], thetas, ps, \"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |00>\")\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps[\"|++>\"], thetas, ps, \"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |++>\")\n",
        "heatmap(delta_map, thetas, ps, \"AOI distance delta(theta,p) = min_q ||E_{theta,p} - (D_qD_q)||_ (symmetric)\")\n",
        "heatmap(q_best_map, thetas, ps, \"Best-fit q*(theta,p) in symmetric admissible family\")"
      ]
    },

        "I2 = np.eye(2, dtype=complex)\n",
        "X = np.array([[0, 1], [1, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Y = np.array([[0, -1j], [1j, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Z = np.array([[1, 0], [0, -1]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Channels via Kraus operators\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def apply_kraus(rho, kraus_ops):\n",
        "    out = np.zeros_like(rho, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for K in kraus_ops:\n",
        "        out += K @ rho @ dagger(K)\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "def depolarizing_kraus(p):\n",
        "    p = float(p)\n",
        "    k0 = np.sqrt(max(0.0, 1.0 - p)) * I2\n",
        "    kx = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * X\n",
        "    ky = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * Y\n",
        "    kz = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * Z\n",
        "    return [k0, kx, ky, kz]\n",
        "\n",
        "def unitary_kraus(U):\n",
        "    return [U]\n",
        "\n",
        "def channel_kraus_product(kraus_A, kraus_B):\n",
        "    return [kron(Ka, Kb) for Ka in kraus_A for Kb in kraus_B]\n",
        "\n",
        "def compose_kraus(kraus_after, kraus_before):\n",
        "    return [Ka @ Kb for Kb in kraus_before for Ka in kraus_after]\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Toy physical channel E_{theta,p}\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def U_xx(theta):\n",
        "    XX = kron(X, X)\n",
        "    return np.cos(theta) * np.eye(4, dtype=complex) - 1j * np.sin(theta) * XX\n",
        "\n",
        "def E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p):\n",
        "    U = U_xx(theta)\n",
        "    K_unit = unitary_kraus(U)\n",
        "    K_noise = channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(p), depolarizing_kraus(p))\n",
        "    return compose_kraus(K_noise, K_unit)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Choi matrix and diamond norm SDP\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def choi_from_kraus(kraus_ops, d_in, d_out):\n",
        "    J = np.zeros((d_out*d_in, d_out*d_in), dtype=complex)\n",
        "    basis = np.eye(d_in, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for i in range(d_in):\n",
        "        for j in range(d_in):\n",
        "            Eij = np.outer(basis[:, i], basis[:, j].conj())\n",
        "            Phi_Eij = apply_kraus(Eij, kraus_ops)\n",
        "            J += np.kron(Phi_Eij, Eij)\n",
        "    return J\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_norm_from_choi(J, d_in, d_out, solver=None, verbose=False, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000):\n",
        "    dimX = d_out * d_in\n",
        "    rho = cp.Variable((d_in, d_in), complex=True)\n",
        "    Xvar = cp.Variable((dimX, dimX), complex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    Iout = np.eye(d_out, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    I_rho = cp.kron(Iout, rho)\n",
        "\n",
        "    block = cp.bmat([[I_rho, Xvar],\n",
        "                     [Xvar.H, I_rho]])\n",
        "\n",
        "    constraints = [\n",
        "        block >> 0,\n",
        "        rho >> 0,\n",
        "        cp.trace(rho) == 1\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    objective = cp.Maximize(cp.real(cp.trace(J @ Xvar)))\n",
        "    prob = cp.Problem(objective, constraints)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if solver is None:\n",
        "        solver = cp.SCS\n",
        "\n",
        "    if solver == cp.SCS:\n",
        "        prob.solve(solver=cp.SCS, verbose=verbose, eps=scs_eps, max_iters=scs_max_iters)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        prob.solve(solver=solver, verbose=verbose)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if prob.value is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"Diamond norm SDP returned None; try different solver or settings.\")\n",
        "    return float(prob.value)\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_F, d_in=4, d_out=4, solver=None, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000):\n",
        "    J_E = choi_from_kraus(kraus_E, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    J_F = choi_from_kraus(kraus_F, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    return diamond_norm_from_choi(J_E - J_F, d_in, d_out, solver=solver, verbose=False,\n",
        "                                 scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Symmetric admissible family:\n",
        "#   C_q = (D_q  D_q)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def C_q_kraus(q):\n",
        "    return channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(q), depolarizing_kraus(q))\n",
        "\n",
        "def estimate_delta_min_over_q(theta, p, q_grid, solver=None, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000):\n",
        "    if abs(theta) < 1e-12:\n",
        "        return 0.0, p\n",
        "    kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p)\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    best_q = None\n",
        "    for q in q_grid:\n",
        "        kraus_C = C_q_kraus(q)\n",
        "        dn = diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_C, solver=solver,\n",
        "                                               scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters)\n",
        "        if (best is None) or (dn < best):\n",
        "            best = dn\n",
        "            best_q = q\n",
        "    return best, best_q\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Two inputs: |00> and |++>\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def ket0():\n",
        "    return np.array([1, 0], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def ket1():\n",
        "    return np.array([0, 1], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def ket_plus():\n",
        "    return (1/np.sqrt(2)) * (ket0() + ket1())\n",
        "\n",
        "def rho_from_ket(ket):\n",
        "    return np.outer(ket, ket.conj())\n",
        "\n",
        "def build_inputs():\n",
        "    ket00 = kron(ket0(), ket0())\n",
        "    ketpp = kron(ket_plus(), ket_plus())\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"|00>\": rho_from_ket(ket00),\n",
        "        \"|++>\": rho_from_ket(ketpp),\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Run sweep + plots\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def run_sweep(thetas, ps, q_grid, solver=cp.SCS, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000, print_rows=True):\n",
        "    inputs = build_inputs()\n",
        "    I_maps = {name: np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps))) for name in inputs.keys()}\n",
        "    delta_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    q_best_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        for j, p in enumerate(ps):\n",
        "            kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(th, p)\n",
        "\n",
        "            for name, rho0 in inputs.items():\n",
        "                rho_out = apply_kraus(rho0, kraus_E)\n",
        "                I_maps[name][i, j] = mutual_information(rho_out, dims=(2, 2), clip_nonneg=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "            d_est, q_best = estimate_delta_min_over_q(th, p, q_grid, solver=solver,\n",
        "                                                      scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters)\n",
        "            delta_map[i, j] = d_est\n",
        "            q_best_map[i, j] = q_best\n",
        "\n",
        "            if print_rows:\n",
        "                print(f\"theta={th:.3f}, p={p:.3f}  ->  \"\n",
        "                      f\"I00={I_maps['|00>'][i,j]:.6f},  Ipp={I_maps['|++>'][i,j]:.6f},  \"\n",
        "                      f\"delta~{d_est:.6f} (q*={q_best:.3f})\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return I_maps, delta_map, q_best_map\n",
        "\n",
        "def heatmap(data, thetas, ps, title):\n",
        "    plt.figure()\n",
        "    plt.imshow(\n",
        "        data.T,\n",
        "        origin=\"lower\",\n",
        "        aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "        extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]]\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.colorbar()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Sanity check: delta(theta,0) vs 2 sin(theta)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def sanity_delta_vs_2sintheta(theta_grid, q_grid, solver=cp.SCS, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000):\n",
        "    deltas = []\n",
        "    for th in theta_grid:\n",
        "        d_est, _ = estimate_delta_min_over_q(th, 0.0, q_grid, solver=solver, scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters)\n",
        "        deltas.append(d_est)\n",
        "    deltas = np.array(deltas)\n",
        "    target = 2.0 * np.sin(theta_grid)\n",
        "    plt.figure()\n",
        "    plt.plot(theta_grid, deltas, marker=\"o\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(theta_grid, target, marker=\"x\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"value\")\n",
        "    plt.title(\"Sanity: delta(theta,0) (dots) vs 2 sin(theta) (x)\")\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Parameters\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "thetas = np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 7)\n",
        "ps = np.linspace(0.0, 0.6, 7)\n",
        "\n",
        "q_grid = np.linspace(0.0, 0.9, 41)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tighter SCS settings to reduce spurious nonzero deltas at theta=0\n",
        "scs_eps = 1e-7\n",
        "scs_max_iters = 200000\n",
        "\n",
        "I_maps, delta_map, q_best_map = run_sweep(\n",
        "    thetas=thetas,\n",
        "    ps=ps,\n",
        "    q_grid=q_grid,\n",
        "    solver=cp.SCS,\n",
        "    scs_eps=scs_eps,\n",
        "    scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters,\n",
        "    print_rows=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps[\"|00>\"], thetas, ps, \"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |00> (clipped)\")\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps[\"|++>\"], thetas, ps, \"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |++> (clipped)\")\n",
        "heatmap(delta_map, thetas, ps, \"AOI distance delta(theta,p) = min_q ||E_{theta,p} - (D_qD_q)||_\\u22c7 (tight SDP)\")\n",
        "heatmap(q_best_map, thetas, ps, \"Best-fit q*(theta,p) in symmetric admissible family\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extra sanity: delta(theta,0) vs 2 sin(theta)\n",
        "theta_grid = np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 9)\n",
        "sanity_delta_vs_2sintheta(theta_grid, q_grid, solver=cp.SCS, scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters)"
      ],

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "def fit_alpha_from_delta(delta_map, thetas, ps, theta_min=1e-6, p_max=0.6, r_min=1e-10):\n",
        "    thetas = np.array(thetas, dtype=float)\n",
        "    ps = np.array(ps, dtype=float)\n",
        "    delta_map = np.array(delta_map, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Build r(theta,p) = delta / (2 sin theta)\n",
        "    denom = 2.0 * np.sin(thetas)\n",
        "    r = np.zeros_like(delta_map)\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        if denom[i] > theta_min:\n",
        "            r[i, :] = delta_map[i, :] / denom[i]\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            r[i, :] = np.nan\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Restrict to p in (0, p_max) and valid r\n",
        "    p_mask = (ps > 0) & (ps < p_max)\n",
        "    x = np.log(1.0 - ps[p_mask])  # negative numbers\n",
        "    results = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Fit alpha per theta\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        if denom[i] <= theta_min:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        y = r[i, p_mask]\n",
        "        good = np.isfinite(y) & (y > r_min)\n",
        "        if np.sum(good) < 3:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        yy = np.log(y[good])\n",
        "        xx = x[good]\n",
        "        # Linear regression yy ~ alpha*xx + b\n",
        "        A = np.vstack([xx, np.ones_like(xx)]).T\n",
        "        alpha_i, b_i = np.linalg.lstsq(A, yy, rcond=None)[0]\n",
        "        # R^2\n",
        "        yhat = alpha_i * xx + b_i\n",
        "        ss_res = np.sum((yy - yhat) ** 2)\n",
        "        ss_tot = np.sum((yy - np.mean(yy)) ** 2)\n",
        "        r2 = 1.0 - ss_res / ss_tot if ss_tot > 0 else np.nan\n",
        "        results.append((th, alpha_i, b_i, r2))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Global fit pooling all thetas\n",
        "    XX_list = []\n",
        "    YY_list = []\n",
        "    TH_list = []\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        if denom[i] <= theta_min:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        y = r[i, p_mask]\n",
        "        good = np.isfinite(y) & (y > r_min)\n",
        "        if np.sum(good) < 3:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        XX_list.append(x[good])\n",
        "        YY_list.append(np.log(y[good]))\n",
        "        TH_list.append(np.full(np.sum(good), th))\n",
        "    if len(XX_list) == 0:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"No valid points for global fit.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    XX = np.concatenate(XX_list)\n",
        "    YY = np.concatenate(YY_list)\n",
        "\n",
        "    A = np.vstack([XX, np.ones_like(XX)]).T\n",
        "    alpha_global, b_global = np.linalg.lstsq(A, YY, rcond=None)[0]\n",
        "    yhat = alpha_global * XX + b_global\n",
        "    ss_res = np.sum((YY - yhat) ** 2)\n",
        "    ss_tot = np.sum((YY - np.mean(YY)) ** 2)\n",
        "    r2_global = 1.0 - ss_res / ss_tot if ss_tot > 0 else np.nan\n",
        "\n",
        "    return r, results, (alpha_global, b_global, r2_global)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---- run fits using your existing delta_map/thetas/ps ----\n",
        "r, per_theta, global_fit = fit_alpha_from_delta(delta_map, thetas, ps, p_max=float(max(ps)))\n",

        "\n",
        "# ---- plot r(theta,p) heatmap ----\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "plt.imshow(\n",
        "    r.T,\n",
        "    origin=\"lower\",\n",
        "    aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "    extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]],\n",
        "    vmin=np.nanmin(r[np.isfinite(r)]),\n",
        "    vmax=np.nanmax(r[np.isfinite(r)])\n",
        ")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"r(theta,p) = delta(theta,p) / (2 sin theta)\")\n",
        "plt.colorbar()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---- plot collapse test: r vs p for several thetas + global model ----\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "for th, a, b, r2 in per_theta:\n",
        "    i = int(np.argmin(np.abs(np.array(thetas) - th)))\n",
        "    plt.plot(ps, r[i, :], marker=\"o\", linestyle=\"-\", label=f\"theta={th:.3f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# global model curve\n",
        "p_dense = np.linspace(ps[0], ps[-1], 200)\n",
        "r_model = np.exp(b_g) * (1.0 - p_dense) ** alpha_g\n",
        "plt.plot(p_dense, r_model, linewidth=3, label=f\"global fit: (1-p)^{alpha_g:.3f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"p\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"r(theta,p)\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Collapse test: r(theta,p) curves and global (1-p)^alpha fit\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"

        "def fit_alpha_constrained_b0(delta_map, thetas, ps, p_max=None, theta_min=1e-6, r_min=1e-12):\n",
        "    thetas = np.array(thetas, dtype=float)\n",

        "    delta_map = np.array(delta_map, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if p_max is None:\n",
        "        p_max = float(np.max(ps))\n",
        "\n",
        "    p_mask = (ps > 0) & (ps < p_max)\n",
        "    x = np.log(1.0 - ps[p_mask])\n",
        "\n",
        "    XX, YY = [], []\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        denom = 2.0 * np.sin(th)\n",
        "        if denom <= theta_min:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        r = delta_map[i, p_mask] / denom\n",
        "        good = np.isfinite(r) & (r > r_min)\n",
        "        if np.sum(good) < 3:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        XX.append(x[good])\n",
        "        YY.append(np.log(r[good]))\n",
        "\n",
        "    XX = np.concatenate(XX)\n",
        "    YY = np.concatenate(YY)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Constrained b=0: minimize ||YY - alpha*XX||^2\n",
        "    alpha = np.dot(XX, YY) / np.dot(XX, XX)\n",

        "    # R^2\n",
        "    yhat = alpha * XX\n",

        "    ss_tot = np.sum((YY - np.mean(YY))**2)\n",
        "    r2 = 1.0 - ss_res/ss_tot if ss_tot > 0 else np.nan\n",
        "    return alpha, r2\n",
        "\n",
        "alpha_c, r2_c = fit_alpha_constrained_b0(delta_map, thetas, ps)\n",
        "print(f\"Constrained fit (b=0): alpha = {alpha_c:.4f}, R^2 = {r2_c:.4f}\")"

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def fit_alpha_beta(delta_map, thetas, ps, beta_grid=None, theta_min=1e-6, r_min=1e-12):\n",
        "    thetas = np.array(thetas, dtype=float)\n",
        "    ps = np.array(ps, dtype=float)\n",
        "    delta_map = np.array(delta_map, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if beta_grid is None:\n",
        "        beta_grid = np.linspace(0.1, 2.5, 141)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Build pooled (p, log r) data\n",
        "    P_list, Y_list = [], []\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        denom = 2.0 * np.sin(th)\n",
        "        if denom <= theta_min:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        r = delta_map[i, :] / denom\n",
        "        good = np.isfinite(r) & (r > r_min) & (ps > 0)\n",
        "        P_list.append(ps[good])\n",
        "        Y_list.append(np.log(r[good]))\n",
        "\n",
        "    P = np.concatenate(P_list)\n",
        "    Y = np.concatenate(Y_list)\n",
        "\n",
        "    best = None  # (SSE, alpha, beta, R2)\n",
        "    for beta in beta_grid:\n",
        "        if np.any(1.0 - beta * P <= 0):\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        X = np.log(1.0 - beta * P)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # best alpha for fixed beta in least squares: minimize ||Y - alpha X||^2\n",
        "        alpha = np.dot(X, Y) / np.dot(X, X)\n",
        "\n",
        "        Yhat = alpha * X\n",
        "        ss_res = np.sum((Y - Yhat)**2)\n",
        "        ss_tot = np.sum((Y - np.mean(Y))**2)\n",
        "        r2 = 1.0 - ss_res/ss_tot if ss_tot > 0 else np.nan\n",
        "\n",
        "        if (best is None) or (ss_res < best[0]):\n",
        "            best = (ss_res, alpha, beta, r2)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if best is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"No feasible beta found. Reduce beta range or check data.\")\n",
        "    _, alpha_best, beta_best, r2_best = best\n",
        "    return alpha_best, beta_best, r2_best\n",
        "\n",
        "alpha2, beta2, r2_2 = fit_alpha_beta(delta_map, thetas, ps)\n",
        "print(f\"Fit f(p)=(1-beta p)^alpha with f(0)=1: alpha={alpha2:.4f}, beta={beta2:.4f}, R^2={r2_2:.4f}\")"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import cvxpy as cp\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# ASSUMES you already have these from the previous script:\n",
        "#   - E_theta_p_kraus(theta,p)\n",
        "#   - depolarizing_kraus(p)\n",
        "#   - channel_kraus_product(kraus_A, kraus_B)\n",
        "#   - diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_F, solver=..., scs_eps=..., scs_max_iters=...)\n",
        "#   - mutual_information(...)\n",
        "# If not, paste this block into the same notebook cell after those defs.\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "def C_qa_qb_kraus(qa, qb):\n",
        "    return channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(qa), depolarizing_kraus(qb))\n",
        "\n",
        "def estimate_delta_min_over_qa_qb(theta, p, q_grid, solver=cp.SCS, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000):\n",
        "    kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p)\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    best_pair = None\n",
        "    for qa in q_grid:\n",
        "        for qb in q_grid:\n",
        "            kraus_C = C_qa_qb_kraus(qa, qb)\n",
        "            dn = diamond_distance_between_channels(\n",
        "                kraus_E, kraus_C, solver=solver, scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters\n",
        "            )\n",
        "            if (best is None) or (dn < best):\n",
        "                best = dn\n",
        "                best_pair = (qa, qb)\n",
        "    return best, best_pair\n",
        "\n",
        "def build_inputs():\n",
        "    ket0 = np.array([1,0], dtype=complex)\n",
        "    ket1 = np.array([0,1], dtype=complex)\n",
        "    ket_plus = (1/np.sqrt(2)) * (ket0 + ket1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def rho_from_ket(ket):\n",
        "        return np.outer(ket, ket.conj())\n",
        "\n",
        "    ket00 = kron(ket0, ket0)\n",
        "    ketpp = kron(ket_plus, ket_plus)\n",
        "    return {\"|00>\": rho_from_ket(ket00), \"|++>\": rho_from_ket(ketpp)}\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_sweep_asym_admissible(thetas, ps, q_grid, solver=cp.SCS, scs_eps=1e-7, scs_max_iters=200000, print_rows=True):\n",
        "    inputs = build_inputs()\n",
        "    I_maps = {name: np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps))) for name in inputs.keys()}\n",
        "    delta_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    qa_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    qb_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        for j, p in enumerate(ps):\n",
        "            kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(th, p)\n",
        "\n",
        "            for name, rho0 in inputs.items():\n",
        "                rho_out = apply_kraus(rho0, kraus_E)\n",
        "                I_maps[name][i, j] = mutual_information(rho_out, dims=(2,2), clip_nonneg=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # exact identity shortcut\n",
        "            if abs(th) < 1e-12:\n",
        "                delta_map[i, j] = 0.0\n",
        "                qa_map[i, j] = p\n",
        "                qb_map[i, j] = p\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                d_est, (qa, qb) = estimate_delta_min_over_qa_qb(\n",
        "                    th, p, q_grid, solver=solver, scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters\n",
        "                )\n",
        "                delta_map[i, j] = d_est\n",
        "                qa_map[i, j] = qa\n",
        "                qb_map[i, j] = qb\n",
        "\n",
        "            if print_rows:\n",
        "                print(f\"theta={th:.3f}, p={p:.3f} -> \"\n",
        "                      f\"I00={I_maps['|00>'][i,j]:.6f}, Ipp={I_maps['|++>'][i,j]:.6f}, \"\n",
        "                      f\"delta~{delta_map[i,j]:.6f}, (qa*,qb*)=({qa_map[i,j]:.3f},{qb_map[i,j]:.3f})\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return I_maps, delta_map, qa_map, qb_map\n",
        "\n",
        "def heatmap(data, thetas, ps, title, vmin=None, vmax=None):\n",
        "    plt.figure()\n",
        "    plt.imshow(\n",
        "        data.T, origin=\"lower\", aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "        extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]],\n",
        "        vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.colorbar()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# Fit: r(theta,p) = delta/(2 sin theta) ~ (1 - beta p)^alpha   (enforce f(0)=1)\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "def fit_alpha_beta_from_delta(delta_map, thetas, ps, beta_grid):\n",
        "    thetas = np.array(thetas, dtype=float)\n",
        "    ps = np.array(ps, dtype=float)\n",
        "    delta_map = np.array(delta_map, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    P_list, Y_list = [], []\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        denom = 2.0 * np.sin(th)\n",
        "        if denom <= 1e-10:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        r = delta_map[i, :] / denom\n",
        "        good = np.isfinite(r) & (r > 1e-12) & (ps > 0)\n",
        "        P_list.append(ps[good])\n",
        "        Y_list.append(np.log(r[good]))\n",
        "\n",
        "    P = np.concatenate(P_list)\n",
        "    Y = np.concatenate(Y_list)\n",
        "\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    for beta in beta_grid:\n",
        "        if np.any(1.0 - beta * P <= 0):\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        X = np.log(1.0 - beta * P)\n",
        "        alpha = np.dot(X, Y) / np.dot(X, X)\n",
        "        Yhat = alpha * X\n",
        "        ss_res = np.sum((Y - Yhat)**2)\n",
        "        ss_tot = np.sum((Y - np.mean(Y))**2)\n",
        "        r2 = 1.0 - ss_res/ss_tot if ss_tot > 0 else np.nan\n",
        "        if (best is None) or (ss_res < best[0]):\n",
        "            best = (ss_res, alpha, beta, r2)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if best is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"No feasible beta found; reduce beta range or check p values.\")\n",
        "    _, alpha_best, beta_best, r2_best = best\n",
        "    return alpha_best, beta_best, r2_best\n",
        "\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# RUN (asymmetric admissible family)\n",
        "# ------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "thetas = np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 7)\n",
        "ps = np.linspace(0.0, 0.6, 7)\n",
        "\n",
        "# keep q grid moderate; this is (len(q)^2) SDPs per (theta,p)\n",
        "q_grid = np.linspace(0.0, 0.9, 19)\n",
        "\n",
        "solver = cp.SCS\n",
        "scs_eps = 1e-7\n",
        "scs_max_iters = 200000\n",
        "\n",
        "I_maps_asym, delta_asym, qa_map, qb_map = run_sweep_asym_admissible(\n",
        "    thetas, ps, q_grid, solver=solver, scs_eps=scs_eps, scs_max_iters=scs_max_iters, print_rows=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps_asym[\"|00>\"], thetas, ps, \"I(A:B) on |00> (clipped)\")\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps_asym[\"|++>\"], thetas, ps, \"I(A:B) on |++> (should be ~0)\", vmin=0.0, vmax=1e-6)\n",
        "heatmap(delta_asym, thetas, ps, \"delta(theta,p) = min_{qa,qb} ||E - (D_qaD_qb)||_ (asymmetric)\")\n",
        "heatmap(qa_map, thetas, ps, \"qa*(theta,p) in asymmetric admissible family\")\n",
        "heatmap(qb_map, thetas, ps, \"qb*(theta,p) in asymmetric admissible family\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fit scaling on asymmetric delta\n",
        "beta_grid = np.linspace(0.5, 2.5, 401)\n",
        "alpha_fit, beta_fit, r2_fit = fit_alpha_beta_from_delta(delta_asym, thetas, ps, beta_grid)\n",
        "print(f\"ASYM fit f(p)=(1-beta p)^alpha: alpha={alpha_fit:.4f}, beta={beta_fit:.4f}, R^2={r2_fit:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Optional: collapse plot\n",
        "r_asym = np.full_like(delta_asym, np.nan, dtype=float)\n",
        "for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "    denom = 2.0*np.sin(th)\n",
        "    if denom > 1e-10:\n",
        "        r_asym[i, :] = delta_asym[i, :] / denom\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "    if th < 1e-10:\n",
        "        continue\n",
        "    plt.plot(ps, r_asym[i, :], marker=\"o\", linestyle=\"-\", label=f\"theta={th:.3f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "p_dense = np.linspace(ps[0], ps[-1], 200)\n",
        "r_model = (1.0 - beta_fit*p_dense)**alpha_fit\n",

      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Redefine the fit_alpha_beta_from_delta function from I3JwRbtiIhhq\n",
        "def fit_alpha_beta_from_delta(delta_map, thetas, ps, beta_grid):\n",
        "    thetas = np.array(thetas, dtype=float)\n",
        "    ps = np.array(ps, dtype=float)\n",
        "    delta_map = np.array(delta_map, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    P_list, Y_list = [], []\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        denom = 2.0 * np.sin(th)\n",
        "        if denom <= 1e-10:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        r = delta_map[i, :] / denom\n",
        "        good = np.isfinite(r) & (r > 1e-12) & (ps > 0)\n",
        "        P_list.append(ps[good])\n",
        "        Y_list.append(np.log(r[good]))\n",
        "\n",
        "    P = np.concatenate(P_list)\n",
        "    Y = np.concatenate(Y_list)\n",
        "\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    for beta in beta_grid:\n",
        "        if np.any(1.0 - beta * P <= 0):\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "        X = np.log(1.0 - beta * P)\n",
        "        alpha = np.dot(X, Y) / np.dot(X, X)\n",
        "        Yhat = alpha * X\n",
        "        ss_res = np.sum((Y - Yhat)**2)\n",
        "        ss_tot = np.sum((Y - np.mean(Y))**2)\n",
        "        r2 = 1.0 - ss_res/ss_tot if ss_tot > 0 else np.nan\n",
        "        if (best is None) or (ss_res < best[0]):\n",
        "            best = (ss_res, alpha, beta, r2)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if best is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"No feasible beta found; reduce beta range or check p values.\")\n",
        "    _, alpha_best, beta_best, r2_best = best\n",
        "    return alpha_best, beta_best, r2_best\n",
        "\n",
        "# Recalculate alpha_fit and beta_fit\n",
        "beta_grid = np.linspace(0.5, 2.5, 401)\n",
        "alpha_fit, beta_fit, r2_fit = fit_alpha_beta_from_delta(delta_asym, thetas, ps, beta_grid)\n",
        "print(f\"Recalculated ASYM fit: alpha={alpha_fit:.4f}, beta={beta_fit:.4f}, R^2={r2_fit:.4f}\")"
      ],
